es and backed by climate scientists and athletes had warned about the dangers posed by extreme high temperatures.\", \"from\": 947, \"to\": 1102, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A report\", \"from\": 947, \"to\": 955}, {\"ngram\": \"June\", \"from\": 968, \"to\": 972}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 982, \"to\": 991}, {\"ngram\": \"climate scientists\", \"from\": 1006, \"to\": 1024}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 1029, \"to\": 1037}, {\"ngram\": \"the dangers\", \"from\": 1055, \"to\": 1066}, {\"ngram\": \"extreme high temperatures\", \"from\": 1076, \"to\": 1101}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris has been struck by a series of record heatwaves in recent years.\", \"from\": 1104, \"to\": 1174, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1104, \"end\": 1109, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.025161924178252e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a series\", \"from\": 1129, \"to\": 1137}, {\"ngram\": \"record heatwaves\", \"from\": 1141, \"to\": 1157}, {\"ngram\": \"recent years\", \"from\": 1161, \"to\": 1173}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At Roland Garros, where Rafael Nadal and Carlos Alcaraz were in action in men's doubles, stadium announcers urged tennis fans to take breaks from the searing heat in cooler areas of the grounds.\", \"from\": 1176, \"to\": 1370, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1179, \"end\": 1192, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Open\", \"score\": 0.9998179795979059, \"rank\": 0.00018205352826768752, \"text\": \"Roland Garros\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Open\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Open\"}, {\"begin\": 1200, \"end\": 1212, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rafael Nadal\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q1908